The paper focuses on using unlabeled videos to improve static image action recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses self-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves motion representation and augmentation, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
